    <section>
        <h3>How PetSoLive Works</h3>
        <p>PetSoLive is built on a three-layer architecture that separates the presentation, business logic, and data storage layers. This approach allows for flexibility, scalability, and an easy-to-manage codebase. The platform is designed to support a wide range of users, from individuals looking to adopt pets to shelters, veterinarians, and animal welfare organizations. The technical structure includes:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> The user interface is built using ASP.NET MVC, HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript, ensuring the platform is both responsive and user-friendly.</li>
            <li><strong>Backend:</strong> The business logic and API management are handled by ASP.NET Core, which ensures fast and efficient communication between the frontend and backend.</li>
            <li><strong>Database:</strong> All user data and media files are stored securely in Microsoft SQL Server, ensuring the platform can scale with increasing data.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

